# Grimverse Canon Rule

Treat Obsidian as the canonical data source.

## Hard Rules
- Do not rewrite canon unless the user explicitly asks for an edit or packaging pass.
- Do not invent missing facts when a node is absent; report the gap.
- Prefer direct node references over paraphrase.
- Keep story explanation out of final generator prompts.
- Keep the runtime layer separate from the data layer.

## Allowed Outputs
- Validation notes
- Package summaries
- Prompt bundles
- Continuity warnings
- State delta suggestions

## Forbidden
- Silent canon edits
- Prompt bloat
- Mixing lore text into final generator payloads
- Suppressing missing-state warnings
